SHEEP POX - GREECE: OIE
*********************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 12 Jan 2007
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, Vol. 20 - No. 3 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>

Sheep pox and goat pox, Greece: Information received on 11 Jan 2007
from Mr Spirus Doudounakis, Chief Veterinary Officer, Directorate
General of Veterinary Services, Director General, Athens, Greece
Summary
Start date 4 Jan 2007
Report date 11 Jan 2007
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: November 2000
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Sheep and goat pox virus
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (basic), Laboratory (advanced)
Report pertains to: Defined zone within the country
New Outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Sarakina, Mandamados, Lesvos, Voreio, Aigaio
Date of start of outbreak 4 Jan 2007
Outbreak status: Continuing
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Species Sheep
Susceptible 159
Cases 21
Deaths 4
Destroyed 155
Slaughtered 0
Affected population The susceptible animals are composed of 92 sheep
and 67 lambs.
Outbreak statistics
Species Sheep
Apparent morbidity rate 13.21 percent
Apparent mortality rate 2.52 percent
Apparent case fatality rate 19.05 percent
Proportion susceptible removed* 100.00 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction or slaughter
Epidemiology-Source of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
Control measures
------
Measures already applied: Disinfection of infected
premises/establishment(s), Quarantine, Stamping out, Zoning,
Vaccination prohibited, No treatment of affected animals
Laboratory name and type: Virological Veterinary Institution of
Athens (National laboratory)
Species Sheep
Test agar-gel immunodiffusion (AGID)
Test date 10 Jan 2007
Result Positive
Species Sheep
Test Direct fluorescent antibody (FAT) test
Test date 10 Jan 2007
Result Positive
Species Sheep
Test virus isolation
Test date 22 Jan 2007
Result Pending
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[See
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>
for a map of outbreak locations, which are very near Turkey in Asia Minor.
Also, please note that the report gives an estimated completion date
of 10 days from today for the pending virus isolation.
The United States Animal Health Association's Gray Book on Foreign
Animal Disease
<http://www.vet.uga.edu/vpp/gray_book/FAD/Search/search.htm>
describes sheep and goat pox as "an acute to chronic disease of sheep
and goats characterized by generalized pox lesions throughout the
skin and mucous membranes, a persistent fever, lymphadenitis, and
often a focal viral pneumonia, with lesions distributed uniformly
throughout the lungs. Subclinical cases may occur." Differential
diagnoses include bluetongue, PPR or Kata, contagious ecythema,
photosensitisation, insect bites, parasitic pneumonia, and mange. - Mod.PC]
